Rating: 3
I only rated this recipe as 3 forks because I felt that it benefited from some modification. Adding cranberries instead of raisins was perfect. I added more serrano pepper than recommended. I also added a habanero pepper to the mix. It adds some smouldering heat to balance the punch of serrano. I used red bell pepper instead of green and Kalamata olives instead of green olives. I also omitted the cloves (which I didn't miss). I also recommend using a portion of the serrano pepper and garlic (planed,not just peeled) while browning the chicken (otherwise, it could be bland). Truly flavorful!

