Rating: 3
This is a good weeknight dinner - - I've made it 2x now and made a few changes to suit my family's tastes, like quadrupling the garlic (some minced, some sliced) and also browning the chicken with some of it; and used about 2x the olives (moroccan cured was all I had) . Also used boneless skinless thighs + chicken drumsticks instead of whole thighs. I think the tastes of the dish are wonderful. What I don't like about the recipe is that it takes about 40 minutes to cook, b/c the rice grains get unevenly cooked - some are mushy and some are too hard. Maybe next time I will just place the chicken on top of the rice instead of "pressing" it into the rice, so the grains get the maximum contact with the broth. Oh, I added about 1 1/2 tsp. of the sambal - - I thought 1 tsp would be too tame and I was wrong! Good thing we can take it hot.

